AN 81-YEAR-OLD woman was left with a broken hip after her bag was snatched in a daylight robbery. Bag-snatch thug breaks OAP's hip AN 81-YEAR-OLD woman was left with a broken hip after her bag was snatched in a daylight robbery.The victim was pushed to the ground in a close in Leslie Street, in Pollokshields, on Wednesday and taken to Glasgow's Victoria Infirmary.She was said to be in a stable condition following the robbery at 1.30pm.Detective Inspector Alan McAlpine, of Govan CID, said it was a &quot;particularly despicable incident involving an 81-year-old woman going about her daily life.&quot;He said the thief had targeted her because of her vulnerability.He said: &quot;Clearly, this was a frightening event for the victim, which has left her in hospital.&quot;We've made door-to- door inquiries and we continue to analyse CCTV. I ask anyone with relevant information on the incident or the suspect to get in touch.&quot; 